title: Knife River Indian Villages National Historic Site: Photo Gallery
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Photos & Multimedia     Photo Gallery              Photo Gallery                    Robinson Collection Items   9 Photos  George and Janet Robinson came to the Dakotas in 1883 and opened a mercantile store in Coal Harbor. Because of their fair trading practices, they exchanged many gifts with some of the Indians they did business with.
